11:
That force, those moves...
There's no doubt about it—the tiger 
before us truly is King Whitetail! We 
must inform the chief at once.
14:
No, don't—
Don't worry, I'll pass the news on to 
him!
16:
There might still be dogfolk soldiers in 
the area, so you should hide with the 
other seniors! Take care, okay?
22:
Man, that was some slick work! 
They don't call you king for nothing, 
do they?
26:
I was totally blown away! I can't 
believe I'm talking to a living legend! 
This is so AWESOME! You're JUST LIKE 
the stories!
33:
Claw, was it? If I hear you spout 
anymore of that king crap, 
you'll regret it.
40:
Nimbus? Sure, dudes, whatever floats 
your boat. Who're the bald kids with 
you? Your escort?
45:
Bald?! They aren't—
Ahem. We are Nimbus's companions, 
not his escort.
49:
Hey there, little buddy! Man, I must not 
get out enough. I've never seen flying 
rabbits or, uh... monkeyfolk? 
Where are you guys from?
57:
Do you EVER shut up? It's like you're 
TRYING to be annoying.
61: Heh! I get that a lot!
66:
I don't know exactly how to explain 
this, but we're not from around here. 
At all.
68:
We don't know where we are, but...
Are... are you at war?
72:
...You really aren't from around here.
Yeah, we're at war. Us and the dogfolk.
76:
And it looks like you have front-row 
seats to the next battle! Look out!
86: WHEW! That sure was a close one!
93:
Well, would you look at that? 
The scouts were right!
94:
Hello there, Whitetail. I think the two 
of us are gonna have a REAL grand 
time! Bwahaha!
99:
I'm sick of it! I've got a name, 
and it's Nimbus!
